From: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
Date: Sat, 8 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: hpe-gxp: add I2C passthrough node

Add the I2C passthrough controller node to the GXP device tree.
The node references the CSM syscon for register access and consumes
the host_power regulator to detect power state changes. It exposes
itself as the i2c_passthrough regulator label for use as a supply
by downstream I2C client drivers (sbtsi, sbrmi, spd5118) in
platform-specific overlay files.

Upstream-Status: Pending
Signed-off-by: Christian Walter <christian.walter@9elements.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/hpe/hpe-gxp.dts | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/hpe/hpe-gxp.dts b/arch/arm/boot/dts/hpe/hpe-gxp.dts
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/hpe/hpe-gxp.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/hpe/hpe-gxp.dts
@@ -534,4 +534,11 @@ fanctrl: fan-controller@c1000c00 {
 			fan-supply = <&host_power>;
 		};

+		i2c_passthrough: i2c-passthrough {
+			compatible = "hpe,gxp-i2c-passthrough";
+			hpe,csm = <&csm>;
+			host-power-supply = <&host_power>;
+			regulator-name = "i2c-passthrough";
+		};
+
 		spifi1: spi@c0000280 {
-- 
